    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bad Choice for Vieques</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Norma Ramos letter charges that compansation offer to Vieques is blackmail by US military authorities who want to keep occupying Puerto Rican island (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Federal Agents Clear Puerto Rican Bombing Range of Protesters'' (news article, May 5):</p>
        <p>You report that a $90 million compensation plan has been offered to Puerto Rico if the Commonwealth allows the Navy to continue its destructive occupation of Vieques. This $90 million carrot amounts to nothing short of environmental blackmail.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Federal Agents Clear Puerto Rican Bombing Range of Protesters'' (news article, May 5):</p>
        <p>You report that a $90 million compensation plan has been offered to Puerto Rico if the Commonwealth allows the Navy to continue its destructive occupation of Vieques. This $90 million carrot amounts to nothing short of environmental blackmail.</p>
        <p>One has to ask: under what circumstances would a people trade away the health of their environment and their own health? This is an unconscionable choice to put before the people of Vieques. The environmental movement in the United States should not stand for this. Only a colonial power would think of doing such a thing.</p>
        <p>NORMA RAMOS  New York, May 5, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is an environmental lawyer.</p>
      </block>
